The paper focuses on developing a deep convolutional spiking neural network for digit recognition, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The use of spike-timing-dependent plasticity (STDP) and reward-modulated STDP (R-STDP) also suggests a focus on neural networks and their learning mechanisms, which falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper's emphasis on energy efficiency and hardware compatibility suggests a potential focus on systems and control (cs.SY).
